1- Full Fine-Tuning?

Imagine Llama has 7 billion weights.
Full fine-tuning changes all 7 billion.
=> Very expensive.
=> Needs powerful GPUs.

2- LoRA?

Instead of changing everything,
LoRA changes only a tiny part.
Think of it like this.
Original book with 1000 pages.
Need cybersecurity knowledge.
Would you rewrite all 1000 pages?
No.
You add a small appendix.
=> That's LoRA.

3- Why use LoRA instead of Full Fine-Tuning?

We used LoRA because updating all the model parameters would require much more computational power. 
LoRA lets us fine-tune the model efficiently by training only a small number of additional parameters.
